text: Rasbora naggsi is a minnow endemic to Sri Lanka. The fish was discovered from a stream running across the Sabaragamuwa Campus in Belihul-Oya, Sri Lanka. This species is named after the famous malacologist Fred Naggs. ==See also== * Rasbora armitagei == References == Category:Rasboras Category:Fish described in 2010
title: Rasbora naggsi
